author: reboot

comments.content: It appears to be **Packard** , although I’m not aware of any decent digital versions available...

Nick is probably correct that there aren’t any really well made digital Packards out there. The two I’m aware of are from [Dieter Steffmann](http://web.archive.org/web/20080830003631/http:/www.moorstation.org/typoasis/designers/steffmann/samples/p/packard.htm) and, reportedly, [Opti](http://web.archive.org/web/20080830003631/http:/www.castcraft-software.com/homepage.html).

The typeface, by the way, dates all the way back to 1913 (Ozwald Cooper).
